   <div class="academics-portraits section dark-gray" data-click-action="portraits"> 
    <div class="container"> 
     <h3 class="cu-headline"> Cornell Portraits </h3> 
     <div class="cu-tabs dark dropdown" data-target="#academic-portraits-list"> 
      <div class="tab-indicator"></div> 
      <a class="tab-selected" href="#" title="Choose another profile"> Fredrik Logevall </a> 
      <a class="tab current" href="#" title="Fredrik Logevall, 2013 Pulitzer Prize Winner"> Fredrik Logevall </a> 
      <a class="tab" href="#" title="Abena Sackey Ojetayo, Project Engineer"> Abena Sackey Ojetayo </a> 
      <a class="tab" href="#" title="Avery August, Professor and chair of the Department of Microbiology and Immunology"> Avery August </a> 
      <a class="tab" href="#" title="Tanzeem Choudhury, Associate Professor in Information Science"> Tanzeem Choudhury </a> 
     </div> 
     <div id="academic-portraits-list" class="tab-panels"> 
      <div class="portrait tab-panel"> 
       <div class="portrait-video"> 
        <div class="video-wrapper" id="fredrik-logevall"> 
         <a class="media-video" data-slug="Fredrik Logevall: Pulitzer Prize-winning professor and vice provost describes Embers of War" href="//cdnsecakmi.kaltura.com/p/537811/sp/53781100/download/entry_id/1_nqefr307/flavor/1_0cirfi3j" title="Play video" data-target="#fredrik-logevall" data-embed="<iframe class='video' src='//www.cornell.edu/video/fredrik-logevall/embed/autoplay' scrolling='no' width='100%' height='100%' frameborder='0'></iframe>"> <img alt="" class="media-img" src="/assets/video/1_sifi0rw4.jpg"> 
          <div class="media-play-overlay"></div> </a> 
        </div> 
       </div> 
       <div class="portrait-info"> 
        <div class="portrait-name">
          Fredrik Logevall 
        </div> 
        <div class="portrait-position">
          Vice Provost for International Affairs 
        </div> 
        <div class="portrait-byline">
          2013 Pulitzer Prize Winner 
        </div> 
        <div class="portrait-copy">
          Fredrik Logevall, a professor of history with expertise in U.S. foreign relations, sets the context for his Pulitzer Prize-winning book, Embers of War. The 11-year project tells the story of how both powers lost their way and how their officials chose war over a political solution. 
        </div> 
       </div> 
      </div> 
      <div class="portrait tab-panel"> 
       <div class="portrait-video"> 
        <div class="video-wrapper" id="abena-sackey-ojetayo"> 
         <a class="media-video" data-slug="Abena Sackey Ojetayo: Technology and Sustainability--Pushing the Boundaries" href="//cdnsecakmi.kaltura.com/p/537811/sp/53781100/download/entry_id/1_ueikw1uq/flavor/1_f67p468t" title="Play video" data-target="#abena-sackey-ojetayo" data-embed="<iframe class='video' src='//www.cornell.edu/video/abena-sackey-ojetayo/embed/autoplay' scrolling='no' width='100%' height='100%' frameborder='0'></iframe>"> <img alt="" class="media-img" src="/assets/video/1_1knzzu7e.jpg"> 
          <div class="media-play-overlay"></div> </a> 
        </div> 
       </div> 
       <div class="portrait-info"> 
        <div class="portrait-name">
          Abena Sackey Ojetayo 
        </div> 
        <div class="portrait-position">
          Project Engineer 
        </div> 
        <div class="portrait-byline">
          Facilities Services 
        </div> 
        <div class="portrait-copy">
          It's an engineer's dream: design Cornell Tech's campus in New York City with a green infrastructure that is a model of sustainability. Happily, it is Abena Sackey Ojetayo's current focus. With bachelor's and master's degrees from the College of Engineering, Ojetayo is a LEED accredited professional and one of the 10 New Faces of Civil Engineering for 2013. 
        </div> 
       </div> 
      </div> 
      <div class="portrait tab-panel"> 
       <div class="portrait-video"> 
        <div class="video-wrapper" id="avery-august-asthma-research"> 
         <a class="media-video" data-slug="Avery August targets asthma in animals and humans" href="//cdnsecakmi.kaltura.com/p/537811/sp/53781100/download/entry_id/0_owv36dx0/flavor/1_uxqvxtjl" title="Play video" data-target="#avery-august-asthma-research" data-embed="<iframe class='video' src='//www.cornell.edu/video/avery-august-asthma-research/embed/autoplay' scrolling='no' width='100%' height='100%' frameborder='0'></iframe>"> <img alt="" class="media-img" src="/assets/images/avery-august.jpg"> 
          <div class="media-play-overlay"></div> </a> 
        </div> 
       </div> 
       <div class="portrait-info"> 
        <div class="portrait-name">
          Avery August 
        </div> 
        <div class="portrait-position">
          Professor and chair of the Department of Microbiology and Immunology 
        </div> 
        <div class="portrait-byline">
          College of Veterinary Medicine 
        </div> 
        <div class="portrait-copy">
          Conducting research on diseases common in humans and animals alike allows Cornell immunologist Avery August to make discoveries otherwise impossible. Mice, for example, no longer develop asthma when a particular enzyme is targeted. This novel research begs the question: can scientists create new medicines that are similarly effective in humans? 
        </div> 
       </div> 
      </div> 
      <div class="portrait tab-panel"> 
       <div class="portrait-video"> 
        <div class="video-wrapper" id="tanzeem-choudhury"> 
         <a class="media-video" data-slug="Tanzeem Choudhury" href="//cdnsecakmi.kaltura.com/p/537811/sp/53781100/download/entry_id/0_56lq7ggt/flavor/1_djb8mybf" title="Play video" data-target="#tanzeem-choudhury" data-embed="<iframe class='video' src='//www.cornell.edu/video/tanzeem-choudhury/embed/autoplay' scrolling='no' width='100%' height='100%' frameborder='0'></iframe>"> <img alt="" class="media-img" src="/assets/video/1_jxi5h9wf.jpg"> 
          <div class="media-play-overlay"></div> </a> 
        </div> 
       </div> 
       <div class="portrait-info"> 
        <div class="portrait-name">
          Tanzeem Choudhury 
        </div> 
        <div class="portrait-position">
          Associate Professor in Information Science 
        </div> 
        <div class="portrait-byline">
          Computing and Information Science 
        </div> 
        <div class="portrait-copy">
          Smart phones are our constant companions, intimately attuned to our shifting physical and mental states. Through mobile applications such as BeWell, Tanzeem Choudhury is creating new tools that allow us to mine the wisdom of our devices and help us live healthier, happier lives. 
        </div> 
       </div> 
      </div> 
     </div> 
    </div> 
   </div> 
   <div class="academics-world section"> 
    <div class="container"> 
     <div class="cu-large-callout academics-block"> 
      <h3 class="cu-title alt"> In the Field </h3> 
      <div class="media-box"> 
       <img alt="" class="media-img" src="/assets/images/academics/service-project-1200x675.jpg"> 
       <div class="media-overlay vjack"> 
        <div class="vbottom"> 
         <div class="media-caption">
           Students involved in the POST Program help with interior demolition of a house 
         </div> 
        </div> 
       </div> 
      </div> 
      <div class="callout-body"> 
       <h4 class="cu-headline"> Service with a Purpose </h4> 
       <div class="callout-copy"> 
        <p> Public service is a pillar of Cornell academics. It not only enriches the community—it enriches your understanding of how ideas work in the real world. </p> 
       </div> 
       <div class="callout-links"> 
        <ul class="link-list"> 
         <li> <a href="http://landgrant.cornell.edu/history.cfm" title="The history of Land Grant"> Learn About Our Land-Grant Mission </a> </li> 
         <li> <a href="http://www.cornell.edu/outreach/" title="How outreach programs solve real-world problems"> Local Outreach </a> </li> 
        </ul> 
       </div> 
      </div> 
     </div> 
     <div class="cu-large-callout academics-block"> 
      <div class="media-box"> 
       <img alt="" class="media-img" src="/assets/images/academics/student-in-nepal-1200x675.jpg"> 
       <div class="media-overlay vjack"> 
